message.content: *Nordic bronze dagger with human head handle, Basel Gasfabrik find. Typical of late Bronze Age craftsmanship, this dagger features a distinctive human head pommel unique to the Swiss region. Comparable examples are common in southern Scandinavia and northern Germany. Likely traded from the Rhine valley to Basel as a valuable commodity. Part of the Basel Gasfabrik's late Bronze Age settlement deposits. Displayed at the Museum of Cultures Basel, Switzerland.*
